A 49-year-old man is expected to appear in the Klerksdorp Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday for a formal bail application after he was charged on five counts of rape and seven counts of sexual assault. The man appeared in court on Monday after he handed himself over to the police. The charges against him were laid in January and February n connection with incidents or rape and sexual assault that took place between 2015 and 2017. North West police commissioner Lieutenant-General Baile Motswenyane has urged members of the community to work together with the police, to ensure that justice is served. -TNA Reporter